{"id":14881096,"mediaExerciseId":"cab96356-423f-4a00-ae97-627588b4bbc1","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612315,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":238,"solutions":[{"id":6027461,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **Renata needs help to understand the negative protective covenants.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":62,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/1bed5083ecb6e5a655f346f92dbb5d02/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/1bed5083ecb6e5a655f346f92dbb5d02/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A protective covenant is one of the elements of indenture or other debt agreements. A protective covenant is a limitation that does not allow the debtor to take risky activities and put the company in a dangerous position. This limitation protects the lender and helps him receive the money-back.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/f41cd21f2ae01002d2be88863cfefe7b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/f41cd21f2ae01002d2be88863cfefe7b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"There are two types of those covenants: what the debtor should do (positive) and what the debtor should not (negative).\n\n- An example of a negative protective covenant is that while the company is repaying the debt, it can not merge with any other company.\n\n- The consequences of a negative protective covenant can be the prohibition to pay the dividends or issue new debt.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/f08030fe8473b38d7b0b7089a526a535/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/f08030fe8473b38d7b0b7089a526a535/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**This feature makes the bondholders protected, and it lowers the coupon rate. But if the company accepts this feature, the company will have a prohibition to do many activities. So, the management of the company can not do what they want if it is too risky activities.**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/b194acef2f500021fee3bf2e1a3870bf/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/3a297c9ccaad6fef10a6366385922369/b194acef2f500021fee3bf2e1a3870bf/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"1cf984ca-85ba-45b3-b1f8-86be77611199","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active"